<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="448" pageId="1" pageNumber="447" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1719,2033]" pageId="1" pageNumber="447">Female. Integument black, pubescence predominantly grayish white, densely covering head and prothorax, on elytra arranged as a net of irregular patches, each patch surrounded by brownish-black pubescence. Pronotum with five longitudinal stripes of brownish-black pubescence, extending from anterior to posterior border, central stripe wider than others.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1719,2033]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1437,151,896]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="448" pageId="1" pageNumber="447">Lower eye lobes, height equal to that of genae; upper eye lobes well separated, distance between them 1.3 times width of upper lobe. Antennae surpassing elytral apices by about two antennomeres, scape slightly dilated at distal third. Prothorax with minute protuberance at beginning of basal third, slightly constricted behind; punctuation of pronotum restricted to basal row of punctures. Prosternal process slightly narrowed in middle, width equal to ¾ of procoxal cavity. Mesosternal process 1.5 times wider than mesocoxal cavity. Scutellum broadly rounded behind, each side with black mark. Elytra with sides parallel from base to apex, apices emarginate, sutural angle acute, outer angle projected in acute spine. Humeri projected in rhomboid protuberance, anteriorly oblique. Lateral carina well marked from base to distal third. Elytral surface with sparse punctures, mostly restricted to basal half. Legs stout, femora moderately clavate. Metatarsomere I as long as II–III together.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,151,896]" box="[199,1328,295,320]" pageId="2" pageNumber="448">Apical margin of urotergite V truncate; urosternite V narrowing to extremity, apical margin rounded.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,151,896]" pageId="2" pageNumber="448">Male. Antennae exceeding elytral apices by five segments; apical urotergite and urosternite rounded at apex. Protarsi with setae on lateral margins.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,151,896]" pageId="2" pageNumber="448">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,620,404,429]" pageId="2" pageNumber="448">Measurements (mm), male/female.</emphasis>
Total length, 14.6/13.8–16.0; prothorax length, 2.4/2.0–2.5; prothorax width, 4.0/3.0–4.0; elytral length, 11.1/10.0–12.0; humeral width, 5.0/4.5–5.6.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
